						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the Lakshminṛisiṁhasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vikṛiti, Phālguṇa śu. 10, Monday.</hi> On the basis of palaeography it may be assigned to the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It states that the grant of a village Ainampūṇḍi by the chief Vennupāla Sūrananēḍu to god Narasimhanātha of Korlimarla for <hi rend="italic">amṛitapaḍi</hi> offerings. The chief bears a string of epithets like <hi rend="italic">Gaṇḍagōpāla, Chōḍasthāpanācharya</hi> etc.</p>						

						</summary>
